# More info: https://docs.docker.com/engine/reference/builder/#dockerignore-file
# Ignore everything by default and re-include only needed files
**

# Re-include Go source files (but not *_test.go)
!**/*.go
**/*_test.go

# Re-include Go module files
!go.mod
!go.sum

# Re-include embedded shell scripts
!**/*.sh

# Re-include the runner image's per-kind Go text templates. The runner
# Dockerfile (runner/Dockerfile) bakes runner/templates/ into the image
# at /templates/. Without this re-include the seitask-runner build fails
# at `COPY --from=builder /workspace/runner/templates /templates` with
# "not found".
!runner/templates/**

# Per-scenario SND templates consumed by provision-snd's --template. Same
# lesson as runner/templates/**: the seitask Dockerfile COPYs each
# scenario asset dir; without the re-include, builds fail with "not found".
!scenarios/*/**
